annotation.TEXT: First off, let's see what's above the starting point...
It's... boss time? But, I don't see any enemies, so why the boss music?
Nope. Doesn't even spin. So, I'll just be finishing up the level the same way as last time...
Although, I may have to run back and forth several times in some places.
Nothing special over here...
Yep, but what will I encounter, if anything?
And, to the right of this area is...
Ha! Although I don't exactly think this breaks the level, and it looks to me like the player could get here without a cape or Yoshi by going over the top, and then would be trapped.
Can't seem to eat the hammers, probably because they're exactly the same as the ones the Flying Hammer Bros. toss in the original SMW.
Oh, by the way, I tried, but couldn't get Yoshi into that boss door, even as small Mario, so it appears that Yoshi can't reach this level's goal...
The star might still be a good idea to get because of a few overhead munchers, but then again, taking the spring board with you (or simply cape flying) can negate the need for it!
Okay, now it's time for another tour of the Shell Factory. I have to be small Mario for this one.
Although... I never checked out these ? blocks, but they just contain shells. Nothing too special.
A 1-up on a non-turning turn block, and a pipe, which leads to...
Gulp!
Just barely. (I wonder how close I was to dying there!)
Who would've thunk? Chewing on one of those things produces a turtle shell!
Now, in the eversed world... Yoshi's black! Also, did I ever explore to the right of the Thwomp that stomped me the first time I was here?
Well, back to EVW. Now let's see what kind of fun I can have in each of the levels with a cape and Yoshi. For instance, eating this thing produces something unexpected!
Oh, this must be where you start if you start from midpoint. Now, my next question is: What happens if I keep going right?
Let's explore to the right of this area!
...this familiar-looking area, which I already thoroughly explored in an earlier episode.
Oh, a warp! Can I reach it quickly enough?
...nothing! Okay, let's go back and complete the level. However...
More glitchy tongue action... Also, I don't think I ever did explore over here. Well, let's take a look!
Can I go over the top here?
Just be careful with how you maneuver...
The 'rangs are also cape-spinnable, and the dude himself is edible.
Good thing capes are easily farmable here (with the correct switch pressed, of course)!
Boomerangs are tasty, apparently.
Hmm... What's to the right?
Ha! Your purple mushrooms cannot stop Yoshi!
Well? How far does this go? I'm going to have to dump Yoshi soon!
Let's see how dysfunctional I can make Disfunctional!
Moving on to a later part of the level... Yoshi sure comes in handy here!
I can't get it to work, so I guess Yoshi and the key are in the wrong sprite slots. Oh, well... Let's move on with the level.
Oh, I recognize this part. I went through this section on one of my earliest visits, and I used the left warp then, so let's try out the right warp now.
Oh, yeah. Yoshi's tongue is kind of glitchy-looking in certain areas...
This new area seems to have a dark fuzzy infestation...
Yoshi... not so farmable. Since Yoshi n Berry can't be reentered, I can't get another Yoshi if I lose this one!
I wonder why all this is here... Oh, well... Let's rewind a bit and continue the level (sort of) proper.
However, I run into the big ol' end of screen scroll pretty quickly, so I'll just fall down and hit the teleport near the midpoint respawn area.
What's the point of all this?!
If I want to be able to enter a door to activate an aqua switch with Yoshi, I have to shrink myself.
What's this? It looks like part of the level, but I can't interact with any of it...
Double gulp!
Next is... this really complex place. I'm not going to go through every path, but I'll show a few things.
Ow! Okay... Yoshi's feet aren't fireproof here...
So, where else have I yet to explore in this room?
Glitchy tongue... Glitchy head... Yeah, as if I needed any more signs that Yoshi wasn't meant to be here...
This part's kind of narrow for Yoshi, but I think I know how I can get him through!
That guy's not edible.
I think the corner of that brick landed a groin shot on Mario... (Maybe I should send this footage to America's Funniest Home Videos!)
Okay, I guess I'm really done with Shaded Volcano now!
With the power of Yoshi and the cape on my side, I can easily conquer many more obstacles!
Ha! I've got Yoshi, so I don't have to worry about whether something is dangerous or not here!
So, let's try to grab the key while riding Yoshi...
Yoshi should be able to bounce off of the ice block Eeries without any trouble.
Let's see What The Heck I can do in this level...
Wasn't there a moon in there last time I was here? Doesn't matter, as I can't get through the turn blocks anyway...
Can't eat the moving spikes, but I can cape spin them!
Ah, it's a goal. But, what if I didn't take that warp in that autoscrolling vertical area? Cue rewind!
Suddenly appearing cutoff lava FTW!
Those are some weird-looking fireballs... Okay, now I want to do that springboard glitch, but since it might take forever normally, I decided to use some tool-assistance to get it done faster.
I'm pretty sure the fire will still hurt, so let's try to avoid it.
Hey there, mole key! How's it going?
Actually, if you don't fly, this section is quite tricky to get through with Yoshi!
So, I see Yoshi's been eating my blueberry jam again... (Judging by the color of his tongue.)
It's interesting having a spiny as my reserve item (even though I know it's really a mushroom).
Uh, oh. Vertical autoscrolling. So, that's what I gotta deal with here, eh?
Gulp! So much for Mr. mole key. Also, I can't quite get high enough to shortcut here. If only I hadn't lost my cape...
Now, before I leave this level, is there anything special in the block on the ground under the exit teleport?
Oh, bouncy blocks. Better be careful...
But what if I don't wanna "examine close"?
Up and over!
Now, in this part, I could climb up the vine and get the P-switch, but why would I do that?
Look ma! No wings! That is weird though. Why were the wings graphics removed in this hack? (I've seen wingless flying blocks in a couple places too...)
Totally unnecessary level breakage!
Those fireballs look normal... Must've been because of the castle tileset before. Okay, let's try out that warp now.
Can't fly over the top of this area, though...
Let's skip forward a bit...
On top of that, I can stand on these flying things, but I can't interact with anything else over here!
Nothing of interest over there...
Okay, now let's try breaking the level in various ways!
I wonder... Can I fly over the teleport that's here?
A warp... I'll check it out in a moment.

Hello, and... what the heck?! Why are my annotation's letters so big? Hey, YouTube! Why can't I choose my usual 12-point font anymore?! (The only choices are 13, 16, and 28, and this is 13, which still seems way too big!)
Oh, hey! Blue shells! Guess what that means!
Bye, Yoshi!
Looks like it, but what did I just hit my head on?
GULP! (Font size 28, which I probably have almost no use for...)
Flying over the warp point, as usual. (I'm going to do this whenever possible.)
I doubt I'll be able to get in that door with Yoshi, but we'll see...
How effective are the cape and Yoshi against these guys?
Yoshi only protects my feet from spikes, so avoid hitting them from the side or below. Still, there's plenty of places where I can walk on spikes!
Now, Yoshi can stand on the "owow"s and any other damage floors here with no problem, but make sure you watch your head, or you'll go "owow"!
However... this part... will completely stop Yoshi. Nuts! Oh, well. Yoshi's tongue sure is interesting to look at here...
Okay, now this is really weird! It's almost like layer 1 and 2 have switched roles over here!
Also, remember that blue "Safe"s and red "no"s aren't solid. You'll just pass through them.
Let's try breaking Kaizo Breaker next!
Nothing all that useful...
This "bottomless pit" is actually bottomless! Shouldn't I have just bounced out like before? To be continued...
Double gulp! (This one was tool-assisted.)
Let's go up and over the teleport once again...
These spikes can't hurt me! (Well, at least my feet...)
Good thing I can fly, or that part might've been impossible with Yoshi.
Yoshi may be able to walk on munchers, but he can't really handle narrow passages, so I'll have to go over the top anyway.
Bye, Yoshi! Oh, there's the end, with nothing as usual.
I should be able to bounce over the teleport here... (Not recommended without a cape!)
LOL!
Dooooooo, dooooooo... Ha! Screw you, appearing and disappearing blocks!
Interesting, but I can't enter either of these pipes, and what's the point of these ice blocks?
Also, even worse, the default size (this) is 16 now! ARGH, YOUTUBE!!!
Whoops! Careful with that message box Thwimp!
Owww... That ceiling huuurt! Yeah, I still have to watch out for the bottoms and sides of "safe-looking" things.
Well, there's a warp, and through this wall is another warp...

Well, I think this video's gone on long enough, so I'm going to stop here and resume breaking levels next time! But before I end this episode, I want to point out what I think is a level design flaw that I discovered over here...
A shortcut is possible here, and the level can be cleared easily by going left from there, but let's keep going right...
